'''
Create a program that, depending on the steak temperature (in Celsius), returns the cooking level in English.
The user should provide the temperature.

Conditions:

Less than 48°C - Cook for more minutes
48°C to 53°C - Seared
54°C to 59°C - Medium rare
60°C to 64°C - Medium
65°C to 70°C - Medium well
71°C to 85°C - Well done
Greater than 86°C - Burnt

'''

temp_cel = int(input('What is the temperature of the steak? '))

if temp_cel < 48:
    print('Cook for more minutes')
elif temp_cel in range(48, 54):
    print('Seared')
elif temp_cel in range(54, 60):
    print('Medium rare')
elif temp_cel in range(60, 65):
    print('Medium')
elif temp_cel in range(65, 71):
    print('Medium well')
elif temp_cel in range(71, 86):
    print('Well done')
else:
    print('Burnt steak')
